# Command Chat Connect (SPA)

This repository is a **single-page application**: **Vite + React + TypeScript**, with **Supabase** for backend and realtime.

## Tooling

- **Vite + React + TypeScript**; UI uses **shadcn/ui**-style components under `src/components/ui/`.
- **Lovable compatibility**: keep **`lovable-tagger`** in `vite.config.ts` (dev-only). If you sync with Lovable, **`lovable-agent-playwright-config`** may be present for Playwright; `playwright.config.ts` / `playwright-fixture.ts` use it when installed and fall back locally otherwise.

## Deployment and URLs

- Use **`getRegistrationPageUrl()`** for the **`/register`** URL in the browser **and** for CLI **`REGISTER_URL`** (same string). The SPA serves GET; **Vite dev/preview** proxy **`POST /register`** to the Supabase `register` Edge Function (`vite/register-post-proxy-plugin.ts`). Production static hosts need an equivalent POST proxy or registration will fail from the CLI.
- **Environment**: set Supabase and other client-safe values as **`VITE_*`** in `.env` (or your host’s env); read them with **`import.meta.env.VITE_*`**.

## CLI

- **End users**: **`curl \<origin\>/install-cli.sh | bash -s -- \<origin\>`** creates **`./client`** in the shell’s current directory; no repo clone. The app serves **`/install-cli.sh`** and **`/cli-client/*`** from **`public/`**, produced by **`npm run sync-cli-public`** (**`predev`** / **`prebuild`**). Source is **`client/`** + **`scripts/install-cli-remote.sh`**; **`public/cli-client/`** and **`public/install-cli.sh`** are gitignored outputs.

## Conventions

- Prefer matching existing patterns in `src/` (routing in `App.tsx`, data layer under `src/lib/`) rather than introducing a parallel stack unless the task requires it.
